divs: Sighting DetailsGoing through my photos from trip to San Francisco. Sensor on my Canon 20D is very dirty and I am cleaning up my photos a lot these days. Spots appear the most on sky shots, and on this particular shot I saw one spot that seemed to have a density and shape I never seen before or since on other shots from that trip. I have submitted three versions of same photo, one with no photo shopping, one where I cleaned up all spots but one in question and a third with high contrast, removed the color and reduced the noise around the "UFO". Never heard anything or saw anything when I took the photo. It is taken on top of Fort Point under the Golden Gate bridge looking west towards the Pacific Ocean. An interesting sidenote this was taken the afternoon around the time of the Fleet Week air show which included the Blue Angel. Maybe "they" were in the solar system and wanted to check out the show!? First time I picked up something like this, who knows, but it has that classic saucer shape.
